Assignment 3 README

This project implements brain state classification using fMRI data for two datasets:
sub-01/ses-test and sub-01/ses-retest. All required steps (a)–(e) were performed independently
for each dataset, including preprocessing, feature extraction, classification, cross-validation,
and parameter search.

Step (e): Parameter Search

For both datasets, a grid search was performed over the following parameters:

- Brain mask threshold: 0.12, 0.15, 0.18, 0.20, 0.22, 0.24, 0.26
- Number of folds (K) for cross-validation: 6, 8, 10
- PCA components: None (PCA was considered but not used in the final best model)
- SVM hyperparameters:
  - Kernel: linear
  - C values: 0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.5, 1, 2, 5, 10

Other parameter combinations (e.g., PCA-based models or different threshold values) were explored,
but did not achieve better performance than the selected best configurations.


Dataset: ses-test

- Best mean cross-validation accuracy: 89.70%
- Best parameter combination:
  - Brain mask threshold: 0.12
  - Number of folds (K): 6
  - PCA: None
  - SVM kernel: linear
  - SVM C: 0.01
- Number of masked voxels: 18864


Dataset: ses-retest

- Best mean cross-validation accuracy: 85.32%
- Best parameter combination:
  - Brain mask threshold: 0.12
  - Number of folds (K): 6
  - PCA: None
  - SVM kernel: linear
  - SVM C: 0.01
- Number of masked voxels: 18210


Notes:

- Each dataset was processed independently, with its own brain mask, parameter tuning,
  and best accuracy, as required.
- A single-threshold method was used to generate the brain mask from the mean fMRI image.
- Feature extraction was performed by applying the mask and reshaping the data into
  (timepoints, voxel_features).
- Stratified K-fold cross-validation was used to evaluate model performance.
- PCA was explored but not included in the final best model, as it did not improve accuracy.
